## Good First Issues

New to the project? Look for issues labeled **`good first issue`**—these are scoped and mentored contributions perfect for getting familiar with the codebase.

**How to find them:** [GitHub Issues with "good first issue" label](https://github.com/[your-username]/[repo-name]/labels/good%20first%20issue)

---

## Coding Standards

### Language-Specific Guidelines

**[If Python]**
- Follow [PEP 8](https://pep8.org/)
- Run: `black` for formatting, `flake8` for linting
- Type hints required for public functions

**[If JavaScript/TypeScript]**
- Use ESLint config in `.eslintrc`
- Format with Prettier: `npm run format`
- Use meaningful variable names; avoid single letters

**[If Go]**
- Follow [Effective Go](https://golang.org/doc/effective_go)
- Run: `gofmt` and `golint`

### General Principles
- Keep functions small and focused (under 30 lines where possible)
- Add comments for "why," not "what"
- Write tests as you write code, not after
- Avoid deep nesting (max 3 levels)

